sentences: Geza Gedeon (born September 28, 1952), professionally known as Geza X, is an American producer.
He was a personality in the Los Angeles punk scene in the late 1970s.
He is credited as having pioneered the use of the headset microphones now ubiquitous in music.
on the minor label Final Gear in 1982.
In the 1990s, X opened a recording studio, City Lab, with Josie Cotton, and recorded acts like Butt Trumpet.
He achieved his greatest mainstream success in 1997, when Meredith Brooks' "Bitch", which he produced at City Lab, spent 30 weeks on the Billboard Hot 100, peaking at number two for six weeks.
